101
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:08,760
Yes, we want to
tell the employee,

102
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,899
you've done a great
job on X, Y, Z,

103
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,400
because of this, this, and this.

104
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,501
Or whatever reasons
it was the factor.

105
00:04:14,501 --> 00:04:16,500
And we also want to tell
them where they may not

106
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,730
have performed so well.

107
00:04:17,730 --> 00:04:20,019
And maybe why they
haven't perform so well.

108
00:04:20,019 --> 00:04:21,790
And let's look at
some reasons or ways

109
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:24,180
that we can try to
improve the performance.

110
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:26,820
But it's also an
opportunity for the employee

111
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:29,430
to give the appraiser
feedback too.

112
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:32,270
Often the employees hold
valuable information

113
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:33,630
to the organization.

114
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:36,460
And unless someone elicits
that information from them,

115
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:39,979
we can't really get improvements
or changes in the way

116
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:42,780
that we do things
in an organization.

117
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:46,469
An always, the last step is to
